rComments: Reversed class was the worst, lectures were the worst, Orgo was the worst, and this guy did not help.

Beauchemin is a good prof. He tries his best to teach the class, but doing well in chemistry relies on practice so doing lots of exercices are necessary. He's accessible out of class and he is super passionate. He has old exams on Brightspace which are a big help for studying for his exams. Plus, he gives a 1 % bonus and and the best ponderation!
Awful prof.!

He has a great and enthusiastic personality which makes it easy to follow through lectures. He does tend to skip through things or assume things are understood. Sometimes appears to be in a rush... Just need to review a lot yourself and do exercises but he does warn you of this!

Not sure where the negative reviews are coming from. One of the best profs Ive had at university of Ottawa. Hes very smart guy when to Harvard. I think faculty of science is lucky to have him and we are lucky we had him as first years! Thank you for the class.

This class is ruining my life, this guy expects you to teach yourself with poorly made videos and then doesnt explain the important aspects of the class and then chucks it all on a midterm expecting students to just magicially know how to solve his overcomplicated problems.

I wasn't a fan of his lectures. He would spend a lot of time explaining certain things and skip over other things relatively quickly that were confusing and needed clarification. I felt as though he didn't actually teach much and that to do well in the course, you just had to memorize all the reactions.

prof excellent, il explique vraiment bien les concepts et il est tres enthousiaste. ca peut etre un cours difficile mais il faut juste pratiquer les exercices qu'il met en ligne et faire des examens pratique

His midterms and finals are almost exactly the same as the past ones. I mostly focused on practicing those instead of rereading the notes. He is very interesting and teaches in a way that keeps students engaged. So glad I took his class.

If you go to class, do your homework, and study 2 days before exam, you will pass A+. Prof Beauchemin is very nice, he answers your questions efficiently. He's good at teaching but explains very fast so you have to be good at learning by yourself especially for the first midterm. Do ALL the exercices he suggests and buy SAPLING it is a must.

Super nice guy, had him for Orgo I. He really likes to talk about what the future has in store for students and talks about all these opportunities which is cool. The only thing is that his explanations are vague and his lectures don't teach you much. It's a hard class so you really have to teach yourself. Nice guy though.

Unavailable for students and expects us to learn everything on our own. He only does exercices in class, you need to learn the theory by yourself. And his office hours were at 8am, and super crowded. He takes forever to answer emails, sometimes he just doesn't answer them. He asks us to not email him on weekends.

Un très bon enseignant! Aucune mauvaise suprise aux examens si on fait les exercices et tests pratiques. Il est vraiment passionné par ce qu'il enseigne et ça c'est encourageant! (Pas besoin d'acheter de livre!)
Excellent, pas besoin d'être un chimiste pour avoir un A+

This prof is so enthusiastic! He gives a great energy to the class. Beware of his more practical approach, and make sure to view the videos on Blackboard before class. His exams are fair. Makes himself available. Also, you probably won't need to buy the molecular kit...
LOVED him. You need to study and understand (don't learn by heart! you really need to understand) and you can get a good grade. Beauchemin has great office hours so go to them! Very helpful.

If I had to recommend any prof at uottawa it would be him. I did Orgo 1 and 2 and Orgo 3 is amazing ( trust me an not those a+ students) what is expected of you is VERY clear. If you practice and understand his practice exams there's no way you can't get above 80%. The final was rather simple and VER fair , similar to the practice. Take it !!

I did pretty well in orgo 1 and 2, but it did not prepare me well for orgo 3. The class is good and well organized, but covers new theory  - it's different than your typical orgo class (which cover a lot of mechanisms). He gives a lot of practice mid-terms, which gives you practice and mentions the marking rubric.  I felt the classes were a waste.

Dr. Beauchemin is adorable! He is so helpful during his office hours. But, the lab quizzes are so hard and require so much effort, and in the end is just useless background information. The course was actually really fun, and not as intense as ochem 1 labs! you make actual stuff like slime!

Lab manual is very poorly written relatingto an older edition of textbook.  Prelabs appear intended to rob you of marks-Questions are vague and next to impossible to find the answer to.  Very disappointed in this lab - if you don't need it, don't take it.  It is courses like this that make Ottawa U look bad for science degrees.

Très bon professeur.  Raconte de bonnes histoires sans perdre le "flow" du cours.  Je suggère absolument de ce présenter au cours puisqu'il passe à travers de la matière assez vite et donne de bonnes explications.  Les examens sont justes mais les points sont perdus très rapidement - faire très attention aux détails.  Très bon semestre!
Excellent prof! Raconte de bonnes anectodes et est un joyeux personnage sympathique.  Va dire à ses élève que faire pour bien réussir
He is one of my favorite profs of my university career.  I hate organic chemistry, but he made me like it.  His exams are very very hard, but hes always there to help if you have any questions.

Excellent professeur. Explique très clairement et fais de temps en temps un trait d'humour pour alléger la matière. Est très présent dans son cours et totalement impliqué dans la matière : il est passionné. Examens difficiles surtout le final !! Mais on le fait pour lui ! Il est aussi très  attentif aux étudiants qui ne comprennent pas la matière.

I believe he's a great teacher - he's very clear about the subject when he speaks - hes passionate - however telling the entire class (half of whom wish to go to masters of med school) that the average of his final has always been between 50-55% borders on harrassment. This is unacceptable
good
Top level Organic Chemistry Professor.  Separate the men from the boys.
Super bon prof , tres clair et explique bien. Il est severe mais si vous etudier bien pis que vous fait les exercices de RMN ca va bien aller
AWESOME! Simple teaching approach and midterms/exams were representative of the content covered in class. He really boosted my interest in organic chemistry :)
Pédagogie 100%
He's a chiller

Demanding class, pretty fun to have organic with him ut watch out from finals because it has nothing to do with midterm and RMN ans synthesis are ur priorities at the end of this class. gd luck soldiers!!!! hihi

Organic profs don`t dissapoint, him and****nou and both some of the best teaches I`ve had in a while, makes Organic fun for anyone, just watch out for the final... and RMNs aren't as easy as they appear
Midterms were easy...Final was ******* hard !
Yes, this kid is so cool. His exams are very demanding though, he demands perfection.

Beauchemin is THE BEST prof!  Well, after Dr. Desilets!  Awesome course that everyone tells you is hell...  it's not.  He really helps you... go see him at this office, and Louis, the TA is AWESOME!  Honestly, it was my hardest/most demanding class so far, but I succeeded IMMENSELY!  Overall good!;)
Awesome prof, he is so helpful and makes organic chemistry fun!!  He is a true assett to the University of Ottawa and he has the passion that is demonstrated by all great profs.
great professor; very helpful and has plenty of office hours (and T.A. office hours) prior to midterms and exam.  The final exam though was...  hmmmm... weird?

He is the best professor ever! He is so good at what he does and he is so passionate about it too. He is very helpful and he really cares about his student's success. The class was just really interesting because he had a good relationship with his students.
Esay midterms, exam was a ****
What a fantastic prof, always willing to help his students and explains everything very clearly. He's always happy and gladly answer any questions. Best teacher I've had.
He's awesome: enthusiastic, devoted to his students' success, and explains concepts quite well.
